# AMR-GigaWord 200k

# ::id 0 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok in a move widely expected on wall street , argentina said it would stop paying its foreign debt and try to revive its devastated economy by creating jobs and boosting money supply with government bonds .
# ::alignments
(s / say-01
      :ARG0 (c / country
            :name (n / name
                  :op1 "Argentina"))
      :ARG1 (a / and
            :op1 (s2 / stop-01
                  :ARG0 c
                  :ARG1 (p / pay-01
                        :ARG0 c
                        :ARG1 (d / debt
                              :mod (f / foreign)
                              :poss c)))
            :op2 (t / try-01
                  :ARG0 c
                  :ARG1 (r / revive-01
                        :ARG0 c
                        :ARG1 (e / economy
                              :ARG1-of (d2 / devastate-01)
                              :poss c)
                        :manner (a2 / and
                              :op1 (c2 / create-01
                                    :ARG0 c
                                    :ARG1 (j / job))
                              :op2 (b / boost-01
                                    :ARG0 c
                                    :ARG1 (s3 / supply-01
                                          :ARG1 (m / money)
                                          :instrument (b2 / bond
                                                :mod (g / government-organization
                                                      :ARG0-of (g2 / govern-01)))))))))
      :manner (m2 / move-02
            :ARG0 c
            :ARG1-of (e2 / expect-01
                  :ARG1-of (w / wide-02)
                  :location (m3 / market-sector
                        :name (n2 / name
                              :op1 "Wall"
                              :op2 "Street")))))

# ::id 1 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok the international finance corporation -lrb- ifc -rrb- has signed financing agreements to establish the central europe telecommunications agency line -lrb- <unk> -rrb- , a ### million u.s. dollar agency line .
# ::alignments
(s / sign-02
      :ARG0 (c / corporation
            :name (n / name
                  :op1 "International"
                  :op2 "Finance"
                  :op3 "Corporation"))
      :ARG1 (a / agree-01
            :ARG1 (e / establish-01
                  :ARG0 c
                  :ARG1 (l / line
                        :mod (a2 / agency
                              :mod (t / telecommunication))
                        :mod (a3 / agency
                              :mod (m / monetary-quantity
                                    :quant 1000000
                                    :unit (d / dollar
                                          :mod (c2 / country
                                                :name (n2 / name
                                                      :op1 "U.S."))))))
                  :ARG2 (f / finance))))

                        :op1 100))

                  :ARG0 p2

      :ARG0-of (k / kill-01
            :ARG1 (p / person
                  :quant (a / at-least
                        :op1 1000000))))

# ::id 1948 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok the wages and benefits of the u.s. workers increased #.# percent in #### , the fastest growth in four years , the labor department reported here tuesday .
# ::alignments
(r / report-01
      :ARG0 (d / department
            :topic (l / labor))
      :ARG1 (ii / increase-01
            :ARG1 (a / and
                  :op1 (w / wage
                        :poss (p / person
                              :ARG0-of (w2 / work-01)
                              :mod (c / country
                                    :name (n / name
                                          :op1 "United"
                                          :op2 "States"))))
                  :op2 (b / benefit-01
                        :ARG1 p))
            :ARG2 (p2 / percentage-entity
                  :value "1/2")
            :time (g / grow-01
                  :ARG1-of (h / have-degree-91
                        :ARG2 (f / fast-02
                              :ARG1 g)
                        :ARG3 (m / most)
                        :ARG5 (t / temporal-quantity
                              :quant 4
                              :unit (y / year)))))
      :location (h2 / here)
      :time (d2 / date-entity
            :weekday (t2 / tuesday)))

# ::id 1949 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred

(s / say-01
      :ARG0 (p / person
            :ARG0-of (d / deal-01))
      :ARG1 (c / close-02
            :ARG1 (p2 / price-01
                  :ARG1 (s2 / share
                        :mod (c2 / country
                              :name (n / name
                                    :op1 "China"))))
            :time (d2 / date-entity
                  :weekday (t / thursday))
            :ARG1-of (c3 / cause-01
                  :ARG0 (w / warn-01
                        :ARG0 p
                        :ARG0-of (r / regulate-01
                              :ARG1 (m / market)))
                  :ARG1 (r2 / risk-01
                        :ARG2 (m2 / market
                              :ARG0-of (b / break-01
                                    :ARG1 (r3 / record))))
                  :mod (a / another)))
      :ARG1-of (h / have-degree-91
            :ARG2 (l / low-04
                  :ARG1 c)
            :ARG3 (m3 / more
                  :quant (p3 / percentage-entity
                        :value 1))))

# ::id 1950 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred

            :name (n / name
                  :op1 "Clear"
                  :op2 "Blue"
                  :op3 "Tuesday")
            :mod (m / music)
            :topic (a / attack-01
                  :mod (t / terror))
            :ord (o / ordinal-entity
                  :value 1))
      :time (d2 / date-entity
            :weekday (f2 / friday)
            :dayperiod (n2 / night))
      :location (c / city
            :name (n3 / name
                  :op1 "New"
                  :op2 "York"))
      :ARG0-of (o2 / offer-01
            :ARG1 (p / perspective
                  :ARG1-of (u / unique-01)
                  :topic (m2 / memorize-01
                        :ARG1 (t2 / tragedy)))))

# ::id 1951 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok rapid-fire victories by republicans on business-friendly legislation are exposing fissures among democrats who are upset by their party 's response to bills that sailed through in the early days of the congressional session , with the latest example being the bankruptcy measure approved on thursday .
# ::alignments
(e / expose-01
      :ARG0 (w / win-01
            :ARG0 (p / person
                  :ARG0-of (h / have-org-role-91
                        :ARG1 (p2 / political-party
                              :name (n / name
                                    :op1 "Republican"))))
            :ARG1 (l / legislation
                  :ARG1-of (f / friendly-01
                        :ARG2 (b / business)))
            :mod (r / rapid)
            :mod (f2 / fire))
      :ARG1 (f3 / fissure
            :prep-among (p3 / person
                  :ARG0-of (h2 / have-org-role-91
                        :ARG1 (p4 / political-party
                              :name (n2 / name
                                    :op1 "Democrat")))
                  :ARG1-of (u / upset-01
                        :ARG0 (r2 / respond-01
                              :ARG0 (p5 / party
                                    :poss p3)
                              :ARG1 (b2 / bill
                                    :ARG1-of (s / sail-01
                                          :path (t / through)
                                          :time (d / day
                                                :mod (e2 / early)
                                                :part-of (s2 / session
                                                      :mod (g / government-organization
                                                            :name (n3 / name
                                                                  :op1 "Congress"))))))))
                  :ARG0-of (e3 / exemplify-01
                        :ARG1 (a / approve-01
                              :ARG1 (m / measure-02
                                    :ARG1 (b3 / bankrupt-01))
                              :time (d2 / date-entity
                                    :weekday (t2 / thursday))
                              :mod (l2 / last))))))

            :ARG1 (g / go-08

                        :ARG1-of (g2 / good-02))
                  :ARG2 (b / bad-07))))

# ::id 1953 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred

                  :name (n2 / name
                        :op1 "Bryan"
                        :op2 "Rockson")))
      :ARG1 (w / win-01
            :ARG0 t
            :ARG2 (t2 / team
                  :name (n3 / name
                        :op1 "South"
                        :op2 "Amaints")
                  :ARG0-of (s / struggle-01
                        :ARG1 (l / league
                              :mod (p2 / premier))))
            :time (d / date-entity
                  :weekday (s2 / sunday))
            :ARG0-of (b / boost-01
                  :ARG1 (m / morale)))
      :purpose (c / climb-01
            :ARG0 t
            :ARG1 (p3 / place
                  :quant 2)
            :ARG4 (u / up-to
                  :op1 p3
                  :ord (o / ordinal-entity
                        :value "-1"))
            :location (t3 / table
                  :mod (c2 / count-01))))
